    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You just moved to HEDGEHOG HILLS, a small village full of ADORABLE CUTE ANIMAL CHARACTERS!  You get your own HOUSE, and can visit the many places in this PEACEFUL area!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >There you meet STORM THE SWAN, a ZANY and WACKY character who is always SCARED of something.  STORM says there's a MONSTER in the WOODS, but surely, they're only imagining things!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Enjoy this CUTE and EDUCATIONAL 8-bit adventure on your own portable 'Data Kid Entertainment System' available in select toy stores in the California area!  </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3275280/extras/9d37c82a4a569f8cdaa09335e589f991.poster.avif?t=1731754587\" width=640 height=360 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3275280/extras/9d37c82a4a569f8cdaa09335e589f991.webm?t=1731754587\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3275280/extras/9d37c82a4a569f8cdaa09335e589f991.mp4?t=1731754587\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >STORM THE SWAN is an <strong>8-bit style Point 'n' Click / Visual Novel Retro-Horror</strong> heavily inspired by the <strong>era of the Gameboy and children's cartoons of the 80s and 90s</strong>.  You're  a player for the newest children's game for a portable gaming system, but something is happening with the game (as well as the world around you) that is getting increasingly strange and scary.  </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Meet and befriend several cute animal characters in HEDGEHOG HILLS, live and CUSTOMIZE your HOUSE, UNCOVER deep secrets in the game and witness the collapse of your own world.  </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Storm the Swan is another addition to the &quot;Data Time Software series&quot;, or &quot;Date Time Universe&quot;.  </p>",
